# data/sources/ — Helpers, Caches, Registry

You are working in the support layer for the ingest pipeline. The actual ingester scripts live one level up in `data/`; this directory holds the shared scaffolding they depend on.

## What lives here

- `REGISTRIES.yaml` — canonical registry of data sources per country. One entry per source: URL, licence, last_checked, status.
- `*-cache/` directories (`mutualaid-cache/`, `transition-cache/`, `ica-cache/`, etc.) — paginated API responses, keyed by SHA1 of URL.
- Source-specific helper scripts (parsers, scrapers, one-off backfills).
- `backfill_all.ps1` — re-runs every ingester in batch.

Note: `_common.py` lives one level up at `data/_common.py`, not here. It is referenced from this doc because every ingester imports it.

## REGISTRIES.yaml

- Update the `last_checked` field whenever you run an ingester against that source.
- Add new sources here before writing the ingester. Pick a stable `source_name` — it becomes the value of `organizations.source` in the DB.
- Note the licence for every source. CC BY-SA, PDDL, public domain, scraping-permitted, etc. If unclear, mark `licence: unknown` and flag for review.

## Cache directories

- **Never delete** `*-cache/` dirs. They hold paginated API responses to avoid re-fetching during reruns.
- Rebuilding a cache means running the full ingester with `--refresh`, which can take hours and may hit rate limits.
- Cache keys are SHA1 hashes of the request URL. Same URL → same file.
- If a source schema changes upstream, run with `--refresh` to invalidate the relevant cache. Don't `rm -rf` the directory.

## Shared utilities

- `_common.py` (one level up) holds all shared helpers: `DB_PATH`, `get_db()`, `ensure_column()`, `normalize_name()`, `run_post_ingest()`, `normalize_us_state()`, `is_nonprofit_entity_type()`.
- Add new helpers to `_common.py`, not to individual ingesters. If you copy a function across two ingesters, lift it.

## normalize_us_state(value)

`from _common import normalize_us_state`. Always call this before writing `state_province` for any US row. Maps full state names ("Alabama") to 2-letter codes ("AL"). Pass-through for already-2-letter codes and non-US values. This is the most-violated rule in the pipeline — see `WAVE-B-KNOWN-ISSUES.md`.

## backfill_all.ps1

- Re-runs every ingester sequentially. Run after schema changes or shared-utility edits.
- Long-running (hours). Pipe output to a log file.
- Each ingester is idempotent on `(source, source_id)` so reruns are safe.
